
[1]theocracy

   THEOC'RACY, n. [Gr. God, and power; to hold.] Government of a state by
   the immediate direction of God; or the state thus governed. Of this
   species the Israelites furnish an illustrious example. The theocracy
   lasted till the time of Saul.
